}
  REN files|directory newname

Low Memory, Internal

This command renames a file specified
by the file parameter to the new name
filename. Wildcards may be used in
both names to rename multiple files and
to keep certain characters unchanged.

For example, if you have files TEST
and BEST, then after the command:

REN ?EST ????S

you will get the files TESTS and
BESTS.

The external version of REN can also
rename directories. Wildcards cannot be
used when renaming directories.
